title: FEMALE SEXUALITY: THE EARLY PSYCHOANALYTIC CONTROVERSIES
description: Author: Russell Grigg, Dominique Hecq, Craig Smith Publication Date: June 3, 2015 Publisher: Karnac Books ISBN-10: 1782200223 ISBN-13: 978-1782200222 Pages: 314 pages Format: pdf Size: 14M --- The papers collected together in this volume laid the groundwork for contemporary psychoanalytic women`s studies and gender theory. Many of the issues are still relevant today, among them mothering, passivity, hysteria, masochism, object choice, and the complex relationship between gender and biology. Included are papers by, amongst others, Abraham, Deutsch, Horney, and Klein. --- http://dlfeb.com/book/female-sexuality-early-psychoanalytic-controversies/
